  "prompt": "Is there any law in India to secretly report child labour?",
  "response": "Yes, in India, you can report instances of child labor through various mechanisms and platforms while keeping your identity confidential. The government has established several channels to report child labor which allows for anonymity. Here are some options:\n\n1. **Childline 1098**: This is a 24-hour toll-free helpline for children in distress. Calls to this number can be made anonymously, and it is specifically designed to handle cases of child labor and other issues affecting children.\n\n2. **PENCIL Portal**: The Ministry of Labour and Employment has launched the Platform for Effective Enforcement for No Child Labour (PENCIL) portal. You can report cases of child labor on this portal, and the authorities will take necessary action. The portal allows for anonymous reporting.\n\n3. **Local Authorities**: You can report child labor to the local police or child welfare committee without revealing your identity. They are obligated to act on such reports under the provisions of the Juvenile Justice (Care and Protection of Children) Act, 2015.\n\n4. **Non-Governmental Organizations (NGOs)**: Several NGOs work towards eradicating child labor and can take up anonymous complaints. Organizations like Bachpan Bachao Andolan and Save the Children India allow for confidential reporting.\n\nThese mechanisms are part of India\u2019s legal framework dedicated to addressing child labor, ensuring the protection of children's rights and maintaining the privacy of the person making the report.",
